 TEST 008 TS — Flag-selective persistence
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 Purpose:
   Prove KeeperRecord routes to jText file and DatabaseEntry routes to
   SQLite while the other 980000 events stay in-memory only on the persist path.
   Expect higher ops/sec than persisting all 1000000 events.

 Plan: 1000000 in-memory events × 3 runs
   • indices 0..9999     → KeeperRecord  (jText file)
   • indices 10000..19999 → DatabaseEntry (SQLite)
   • remainder           → no persist flags

Flag routing persistence attaches only on the *last* run (previous runs measure clean hot path; final run verifies counts).

